<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Somewhat" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Somewhat,</orth> 1) pron. something: <cit><quote>here is a letter will say s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 128</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this gentleman told s. of my tale,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 84</bibl></cit> (later Ff <emph>something</emph>). <cit><quote>s. we must do,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an old man can do s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.83" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 83</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. we will do,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 193</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>something</emph>). <cit><quote>s. doth she mean,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou givest me s. to repair myself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 128</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) adv. in some measure, rather, a little: <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 3, 14</bibl> (Qq <emph>something</emph>). <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 2, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 4, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 116</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.55" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 55</bibl> (Ff <emph>something</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.394" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 394</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.41" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 2, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 121</bibl> (Qq <emph>something</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>